    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "God has made man on the sixth day in a special way."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In God’s image and God’s likeness, man was formed from clay"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "With a spirit, soul and body, a three-part man"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "God’s vessel was this man."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Man’s spirit needs to take the lead"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "On God to feed. To this, man must take heed."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Our spirit needs to take the lead"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "On life to feed. Then God we will receive."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Man was poisoned by the serpent, the knowledge tree he took."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In the garden, there in Eden, tree of life he forsook."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Man got fallen with rebellion and corrupted within,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "A man with death and sin."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The evil and the good you see"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Is just the fruit of the same knowledge tree."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The knowledge-tree is God’s enemy"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "That Adam ate by the serpent’s subtlety."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Man was driven out of Eden for he was serpentine,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Now a vessel not of glory but of corruption."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Man a flesh became; he is not the same, a man of shame"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "A vessel dead within."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "4"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The evil and the good you see"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Is just the fruit of the same knowledge tree."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The knowledge-tree is God’s enemy"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "That Adam ate by the serpent’s subtlety."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For this cause, Lord, You came from heaven, and You became a slave."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The Creator, the God of glory, became a man to save."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "As the Bridegroom and a Husband for Your wife, Your bride,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Your love flowed from Your side."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "5"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Your love so great nothing can break;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Your love for her You could not, Lord, forsake."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "She’s in Your heart, in Your deepest part."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Your love for her, Dear Lord, You could not part."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Lord, we love You. Lord, we need You; everyday Lord we do."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "We can’t make it. Lord, we hate it when we’re not with You."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You’re so wonderful and so faithful, Oh precious One!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To You we now respond."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "6"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Your love so great nothing can break;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "We now respond to Your love and Your compassion."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You’re in my heart, in my deepest part."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "My love for You, Dear Lord, I cannot part."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    }
